The negotiating committees for theUnited Steelworkers of America and LTV Corp said they havebegun intensive negotiations and have made a "firm commitment"to successfully conclude these negotiations by May one.    They said the talks will cover issues related totermination of pension plans by the Pension Benefit GuarantyCorp for both active workers and retirees, and insuranceprograms for both groups.    The Union and LTV also said they plan to resolve all issuesrelated to the terms of a basic labor agreement and theeffective use of manpower and equipment. Reuter&#3;